/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do not commit its
# Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
# Anchored to the crate root so the cargo-fuzz binary crate under fuzz/
# (a `publish = false` binary, which *does* pin its lockfile) is exempt.
/Cargo.lock
